# Linux Configuration Repository

This repository contains ready-to-use Linux configurations, including aliases and ZSH configurations, to enhance your command-line experience and productivity.

## Contents

1. Bash Aliases
2. ZSH Configuration
3. Other Linux Configurations

## Installation

1. Clone this repository:
   ```
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/linux-configs.git
   ```

2. Copy the desired configuration files to your home directory:
   ```
   cp linux-configs/.bash_aliases ~/
   cp linux-configs/.zshrc ~/
   ```

3. Source the files in your current shell session:
   ```
   source ~/.bash_aliases
   source ~/.zshrc
   ```

## Features

### Bash Aliases

The `.bash_aliases` file includes a variety of useful aliases for:

- Navigation (e.g., `..`, `...`, `~`)
- File and directory management (e.g., `md`, `f`, `ff`)
- System operations (e.g., `update`, `sysinfo`)
- Network-related tasks (e.g., `myip`, `ports`)
- And more!

### ZSH Configuration

The `.zshrc` file includes:

- Oh My Zsh setup
- Theme configuration
- Plugin management
- Custom prompt settings

## Customization

Feel free to modify these configurations to suit your needs. You can add new aliases, change ZSH themes, or include additional plugins as desired.

## Contributing

Contributions are welcome! If you have any useful configurations or improvements, please submit a pull request.

